item.title: Ep #5: Too Many Sweatshirts w/ Ida Lindsey & Ben Frank
item.dc:creator: Mister Baby Podcasts
item.description: This week we sat down with our good friends, and hosts of The Failure Show, Ida Lindsey and Ben Frank. In addition to telling us about being regulars here in the Shanghai comedy scene, they shared their stories of Mississippi funerals, adventurous lunches in Israel, courtroom confessions, and eating cheesesteaks with celebrities.

item.title: Ep #4: Oofty Goofty w/ Tom Weishan
item.dc:creator: Mister Baby Podcasts
item.description: This week we sat down with Tom Weishan to talk about his short lived career at Second City and the DIY sketch/improv scene of Chicago, moments of Hazing students gone wrong, and how he came to Shanghai to perform Josh Groban songs for wealthy Chinese parents in order to close some sales.

item.itunes:subtitle: From a failed Haze Master in university, to Second City in Chicago, and finally impromptu talent shows in Shanghai, our guest Tom Weishan is always ready to accept any challange thrown at him.

item.title: Ep #3: HoneyBadgers w/ Annie Wong, Jenny Wu, & Clarissa Dourmashkin-Cagol
item.dc:creator: Mister Baby Podcasts
item.description: This week Beryl and I sat down a group of ladies from around the world, who have all ended up here in Shanghai at one time or another. Annie, Jenny, and Clarissa share their stories from living and traveling abroad, the wonderlust they feel while working around the globe, and how their adventures have shapes the connections they still have today. Oh, and of course MOOOSH!

Ep #2: Start-ups & Animal Dung w/ Alex Duncan Mister Baby Podcasts Wed, 19 Apr 2017 08:00:00 +0000 https://sean6bucks.github.io/MisterBabyPodcast This week Beryl and I sat down with Alex Duncan our friend and ex-boss to chat about his many business ventures while he's been in Shanghai. We learned about how he took his degree in zoology and turned that into start-ups in the fashion world, the art world, the fly fishing world, and now the tech world.

item.title: Ep #1: Hamburger Stabbing w/ Tim Neesham
item.dc:creator: Mister Baby Podcasts
item.description: This week we sat down with our friend Tim Neesham and heard all kinds of amazing stories from his travels around the world. From trouble with street kids in South America, to hillybillies of the Australian Outback, Tim has certainly seen some things, and that was all before he landed here in Shanghai.

item.title: Ep #0: The Roadtrip w/ Beryl and Sean
item.description: For Episode 0, Beryl and I sat down and just chatted with ourselves as sort of an intro to the podcast. We ( mostly B ) ended up telling the story of our road trip across America, and how it tested our friendship, but inevitably bringing us much closer.
